text.tspan: Core logic of LibrePCB (data structures, algorithms, utils, ...)
- Error handling: Exceptions or something like "isValid()"
- No GUI classes / functionality at all!
- No dependency to window manager (i.e. must work headless)
Within this library, there are different layers on top of each other.
All code must only access code from the same or lower layers,
but not any code in a higher layer!
- layer 1: common (core data structures, algorithms, utils, ...)
- GUI: Catch exceptions thrown in static libraries and show message boxes
- CLI: Catch exceptions thrown in the static libraries and print to stderr / exit with error

text.tspan: Classes / GUI widgets / windows to view and modify LibrePCB data structures
- Provides the undo stack framework and commands to modify libraries and projects
- Contains all the editor logic (state machines etc.)
- Error handling: Catch exceptions thrown in static libraries and show them visually
Library to import EAGLE data structures into LibrePCB
- Error handling: Exceptions or something like "isValid()"
